The '''1983 Women's Hockey World Cup''' was the fifth edition of the [[Women's Hockey World Cup]] [[field hockey]] tournament. It was held from 10 April to 23 April in [[Kuala Lumpur]], Malaysia.

It was won by the [[Netherlands women's national field hockey team|Netherlands]], who defeated [[Canada women's national field hockey team|Canada]] 4–2 in the final.<ref>{{cite web|title=1983 Womens World Cup|url=http://www.fih.ch/en/competitions-33-1983-womens-world-cup-world-cup|publisher=[[International Hockey Federation|FIH]]|accessdate=27 September 2012}}</ref> Host nation [[Malaysia women's national field hockey team|Malaysia]] did not participate in the tournament.

