{{Infobox NRHP | name = Aiken Training Track | nrhp_type = hd | nocat = yes | image = Aiken Trials.jpg | caption = Aiken Training Track | location= Two Notch Rd., [[Aiken, South Carolina]] | coordinates = {{coord|33|32|35|N|81|42|30|W|display=inline,title}} | locmapin = South Carolina#USA | built = 1941 | architect = Coward, Ira | added = May 9, 1985 | area = {{convert|75|acre}} | governing_body = Private | mpsub = {{NRHP url|id=64000760|title=Aiken Winter Colony TR}} | refnum = 85000992<ref name="nris">{{NRISref|version=2010a}}</ref> }}
The '''Aiken Training Track,''' with its banked turns and soft straightaways, was considered one of the best tracks in the country upon its completion in 1941.<ref name = nrhpinv>{{Cite web | last = | first = | author = | title = Aiken Training Track | work = National Register of Historic Places - Nomination and Inventory | date = May 9, 1985 | url = http://www.nationalregister.sc.gov/aiken/S10817702025/S10817702025.pdf | format = pdf | accessdate = 21 November 2012}}</ref><ref name= scdah>{{Cite web | title = Aiken Training Track, Aiken County (Two Notch Rd., Aiken) | work = National Register Properties in South Carolina | publisher = South Carolina Department of Archives and History | url = http://www.nationalregister.sc.gov/aiken/S10817702025/index.htm | accessdate = 26 November 2012}}</ref> Notable surrounding buildings include a stable, shed and grandstand. The track and supporting structures, as well as other (non-historic register) structures may be enjoyed and viewed from the quiet roads that border the large district. The Aiken County Training Track, located in [[Aiken, South Carolina]], was listed in the [[National Register of Historic Places]] on May 9, 1985.<ref name = nris/>
