{{Update|date=November 2010}} {{Infobox football club | clubname = Casa del Benfica| image = [[image:Casa Estrella del Benfica.png]] | fullname = Futbol Club Casa Estrella del Benfica| nickname = ''Las Camieras'' (The Foresters)| founded = 2003| dissolved = 2014| ground = [[Primera Divisió#Stadiums|Andorra Football Federation stadiums]]| capacity = | chairman = | manager = | league = | season = [[2013–14 Segona Divisió|2013–14]] | position = [[Segona Divisió]], 15th | pattern_la1=|pattern_b1=|pattern_ra1=| leftarm1=ff0000|body1=ff0000|rightarm1=ff0000|shorts1=ffffff|socks1=ff0000| pattern_la2=|pattern_b2=|pattern_ra2=| leftarm2=000000|body2=000000|rightarm2=000000|shorts2=000000|socks2=ff0000|
}} '''Futbol Club Casa Estrella del Benfica''' was an Andorran football club from [[La Massana]].
They have been playing in the top flight of Andorra twice in the 2008/09 and 2010/11 season. In 2014 the club was not registered in the Second Division for the 2014/15 season being out of competition and dissolved the same year.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bondia.ad/esports/lentrada-del-ce-sant-julia-la-lliga-es-en-mans-de-la-decisio-de-la-fifa|title=L’entrada del CE Sant Julià a la Lliga és en mans de la decisió de la FIFA|author=|date=|website=bondia.ad|accessdate=15 August 2018}}</ref>
Like [[FC Lusitanos]] the club CE Benfica, founded in 2003, reflected its Portuguese identity. The club also had a good relation with [[Penya Encarnada d'Andorra]].
==Colors and badge==
As the colors and badge are related with the Portuguese club [[S.L. Benfica]]. The traditional club color was red and the badge was a minor varitation of the [[S.L. Benfica|Benfica]]'s sports club.
