{{Infobox weapon |name= IHP Airpistol 0.177 | image= Dihpnational.JPG | image_size = 300 |caption= IHP Airpistol 0.177 |origin=India |type= [[Air pistol]]s <!-- Type selection --> |is_ranged=yes <!-- Production history --> |designer= |design_date= |manufacturer= Indian Hume Pipe Co. Ltd (National Rifles Division) |production_date= |number= |variants= IHP Airpistol 0.22 <!-- General specifications --> |weight=1.2&nbsp;kg |length=350&nbsp;mm |part_length= 165&nbsp;mm <!-- Ranged weapon specifications --> |cartridge= Diabolo air gun pellets |caliber= 4.5&nbsp;mm (0.177&nbsp;in) |action= Break barrel |rate= Single Shot |velocity= {{convert|415|ft/s|m/s}} |range= 10 metres. |max_range= |feed= |sights= Open }}
The '''IHP Airpistol 0.177''' (also known as IHP Scout) is a single shot [[.177 calibre]] break barrel, [[spring (device)|spring]]-[[piston]] [[air]] [[pistol]].<ref>http://indiansforguns.com/viewtopic.php?t=531</ref> It is manufactured by National rifles division of the Indian Hume Pipe Co. Ltd of [[Ahmedabad]], India.<ref>http://www.indianhumepipe.com/Products/SportsRifles/rifleproductgallery.aspx#10</ref> This gun has open micro adjustable sights with [[globe sight]] on the front. It has an adjustable [[Trigger (firearms)|trigger]] and a rifled [[barrel]] although not designed for high-precision shooting. The [[Pistol grip]] is [[wooden]] and heavy but not ergonomic. The gun can not be dry-fired without charging.<ref>http://airgun-india.webs.com/</ref>
